abstract: Advertisements for Fox Business Network turned up exactly where CNBC had contracted for its ads to be.
snippet: Advertisements for Fox Business Network turned up exactly where CNBC had contracted for its ads to be.
lead_paragraph: On the day they had contracted to run advertisements placed by CNBC, two Web sites owned by Dow Jones & Company instead ran ads for that cable business channel’s new competitor, the Fox Business Network.

headline.main: Dow Jones Drops CNBC Ads From Web Sites in Favor of Fox Links
headline.print_headline: Dow Jones Drops CNBC Ads From Web Sites in Favor of Fox Links
